<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-size: 18px;">The following are some frequently asked questions about installing and using ITOM Container Deployment Foundation (CDF).</p><h2 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 6px; padding-top: 0px; border-bottom: none; line-height: 25px; font-family: MetricHPE_Medium; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span id="What_are_the_recommended_deployment_modes_for_CDF?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="What_are_the_recommended_deployment_modes_for_CDF.3F">What are the recommended deployment modes for CDF?</span></h2><ul style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 4px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 18px;"><li>One master node, at least three worker nodes, and a separate NFS server.</li><li>Multiple master nodes, at least three worker nodes, and a separate NFS server.</li></ul><h2 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 6px; padding-top: 0px; border-bottom: none; line-height: 25px; font-family: MetricHPE_Medium; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span id="Can_I_upgrade_the_suite_images_in_CDF?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Can_I_upgrade_the_suite_images_in_CDF.3F">Can I upgrade the suite images in CDF?</span></h2><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-size: 18px;">You will need to&nbsp;log in the management portal, click&nbsp;<b>SUITE &gt;&nbsp;<a class="image" title="22185968.png" style="color: rgb(58, 131, 230); font-size: 15px !important;"><img alt="22185968.png" src="https://docs.microfocus.com/mediawiki/images/f/fb/2018.04/attachments/17859066/22185968.png" width="34" height="36" class="confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail" data-file-width="34" data-file-height="36" style="border: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; width: auto; margin: auto 0px;"></a></b><b>&nbsp;&gt; Update</b>&nbsp;to upgrade suite.</p><h2 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 6px; padding-top: 0px; border-bottom: none; line-height: 25px; font-family: MetricHPE_Medium; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span id="Will_the_logs_located_in_a_pod_be_deleted_when_the_pod_is_deleted?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Will_the_logs_located_in_a_pod_be_deleted_when_the_pod_is_deleted.3F">Will the logs located in a pod be deleted when the pod is deleted?</span></h2><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-size: 18px;">All the suite logs are currently stored within the persistent volume, so you will not lose them if the pods go down. This applies to both on-premise and cloud-based deployments.</p><h2 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 6px; padding-top: 0px; border-bottom: none; line-height: 25px; font-family: MetricHPE_Medium; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span id="How_do_I_restart_the_CDF_cluster_(foundation_components)?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="How_do_I_restart_the_CDF_cluster_.28foundation_components.29.3F">How do I restart the CDF cluster (foundation components)?</span></h2><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-size: 18px;">Run the following commands to restart the CDF cluster:</p><pre style="font-family: Consolas, &quot;Courier New&quot;; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.25em; margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 4px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240); padding: 1em; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: normal;">cd ${K8S_HOME}/bin
./kube-restart.sh</pre><h2 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 6px; padding-top: 0px; border-bottom: none; line-height: 25px; font-family: MetricHPE_Medium; color: rgb(0, 115, 231) !important; font-size: 24px !important;"><span id="Do_I_need_to_add_exceptions_to_the_firewall_policy?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Do_I_need_to_add_exceptions_to_the_firewall_policy.3F">Do I need to add exceptions to the firewall policy?</span></h2><p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px; font-size: 18px;">Browsers access CDF via HTTPS ports (TCP/5443). End users need to add it to the firewall exception policy.</p>
